    117 /**
    118 * Given a resource and a list of ref paths - resolves them all
    119 * @param {Object} obj FHIR Resource
    120 * @param {Object} fhirOptions The fhir options of the initiating request call
    121 * @param {Object} cache A map to store fetched refs
    122 * @param {FhirClient} client The client instance
    123 * @private
    124 */
    125 function resolveRefs(obj, fhirOptions, cache, client) {
    126
    127 // 1. Sanitize paths, remove any invalid ones
    128 let paths = makeArray(fhirOptions.resolveReferences)
    129 .filter(Boolean) // No false, 0, null, undefined or ""
    130 .map(path => String(path).trim())

    132
    133 // 2. Remove duplicates
    134 134 paths = paths.filter((p, i) => {

    137 2 debug("Duplicated reference path \"%s\"", p);
    138 2 return false;
    139 }
    140 68 return true;
    141 });
    142
    143 // 3. Early exit if no valid paths are found
    144 134 if (!paths.length) {
    145 72 return Promise.resolve();
    146 }
    147
    148 // 4. Group the paths by depth so that child refs are looked up
    149 // after their parents!
    150 62 const groups = {};
    151 62 paths.forEach(path => {
    152 const len = path.split(".").length;
    153 68 if (!groups[len]) {
    154 64 groups[len] = [];
    155 }
    156 68 groups[len].push(path);
    157 });
    158
    159 // 5. Execute groups sequentially! Paths within same group are
    160 // fetched in parallel!
    161 /**
    162 * @type any
    163 */
    164 62 let task = Promise.resolve();
    165 Object.keys(groups).sort().forEach(len => {
    166 const group = groups[len];
    167 task = task.then(() => Promise.all(group.map(path => {
    168 return resolveRef(obj, path, fhirOptions.graph, cache, client);
    169 })));
    170 });

    258 /** 117
    259 * Given a resource and a list of ref paths - resolves them all
    260 * @param {Object} obj FHIR Resource
    261 * @param {Object} fhirOptions The fhir options of the initiating request call
    262 * @param {Object} cache A map to store fetched refs
    263 * @param {FhirClient} client The client instance
    264 * @private
    265 */
    266
    267
    268 function resolveRefs(obj, fhirOptions, cache, client) { 125
    269 // 1. Sanitize paths, remove any invalid ones 127
    270 134 let paths = 128
    271 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 128
    272 (0, 128
    273 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 128
    274
    275 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 128
    276 _lib 128
    277 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 128
    278 . 128
    279 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 128
    280 makeArray) 128
    281 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 128
    282 (fhirOptions.resolveReferences).filter(Boolean) // No false, 0, null, undefined or "" 129
    283 .map(path => String(path).trim()).filter(Boolean); // No space-only strings 131
    284 // 2. Remove duplicates 133
    285
    286 134 paths = paths.filter((p, i) => { 134
    287 let index = paths.indexOf(p, i + 1); 135
    288
    289 70 if (index > -1) { 136
    290 2 debug("Duplicated reference path \"%s\"", p); 137
    291 2 return false; 138
    292 } 139
    293
    294 68 return true; 140
    295 }); // 3. Early exit if no valid paths are found 143
    296
    297 134 if (!paths.length) { 144
    298 72 return Promise.resolve(); 145
    299 } // 4. Group the paths by depth so that child refs are looked up 148
    300 // after their parents! 149
    301
    302
    303 62 const groups = {}; 150
    304 62 paths.forEach(path => { 151
    305 const len = path.split(".").length; 152
    306
    307 68 if (!groups[len]) { 153
    308 64 groups[len] = []; 154
    309 } 155
    310
    311 68 groups[len].push(path); 156
    312 }); // 5. Execute groups sequentially! Paths within same group are 159
    313 // fetched in parallel! 160
    314
    315 /** 161
    316 * @type any
    317 */
    318
    319 62 let task = Promise.resolve(); 164
    320 62 Object.keys(groups).sort().forEach(len => { 165
    321 const group = groups[len]; 166
    322 64 task = task.then(() => Promise.all(group.map(path => { 167
    323 return resolveRef(obj, path, fhirOptions.graph, cache, client); 168
    324 }))); 167
    325 }); 165
    326 62 return task; 171
    327 } 172

    377
    378 9 if (!redirectUri) {
    379 1 throw new Error("Missing state.redirectUri");
    380 }

    382 8 if (!tokenUri) {

    386 7 if (!clientId) {
    387 1 throw new Error("Missing state.clientId");

    389
    390 const requestOptions = {
    391 method: "POST",
    392 headers: { "content-type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" },
    393 body: `code=${code}&grant_type=authorization_code&redirect_uri=${
    394 encodeURIComponent(redirectUri)}`
    395 };
    396
    397 // For public apps, authentication is not possible (and thus not required),
    398 // since a client with no secret cannot prove its identity when it issues a
    399 // call. (The end-to-end system can still be secure because the client comes
    400 // from a known, https protected endpoint specified and enforced by the
    401 // redirect uri.) For confidential apps, an Authorization header using HTTP
    402 // Basic authentication is required, where the username is the apps
    403 // client_id and the password is the apps client_secret (see example).
    404
    if (
    clientSecret) {
    405 requestOptions.headers.Authorization = "Basic " + btoa(
    406 clientId + ":" + clientSecret
    407 );
    408 debug("Using state.clientSecret to construct the authorization header: %s", requestOptions.headers.Authorization);
    409 } else {
    410 6 debug("No clientSecret found in state. Adding the clientId to the POST body");
    411 6 requestOptions.body += `&client_id=${encodeURIComponent(clientId)}`;
    412 }
    413
    414 6 return requestOptions;
    415 }

    435 export async function init(env, options)

    442 6 if (code && state) {
    443 2 return completeAuth(env);
    444 }
    445

    447 // instance have already been created in this session and we should try to
    448 // "revive" it.
    449 4 const storage = env.getStorage();
    450 const key = state || await storage.get(SMART_KEY);
    451 4 const cached = await storage.get(key);
    452 4 if (cached) {
    453 return new Client(env, cached);
    454 }
    455
    456 // Otherwise try to launch
    457 return authorize(env, options).then(() => {
    458 // `init` promises a Client but that cannot happen in this case. The
    459 // browser will be redirected (unload the page and be redirected back
    460 // to it later and the same init function will be called again). On
    461 // success, authorize will resolve with the redirect url but we don't
    462 // want to return that from this promise chain because it is not a
    463 // Client instance. At the same time, if authorize fails, we do want to
    464 // pass the error to those waiting for a client instance.
    465 return new Promise(() => { /* leave it pending!!! */ });
    466 });
    467 }

    531 /** 370
    532 * Builds the token request options. Does not make the request, just

    536
    537 function buildTokenRequest(code, state) { 375
    538 9 const { 376
    539 redirectUri, 376
    540 clientSecret, 376
    541 tokenUri, 376
    542 clientId 376
    543 } = state; 376
    544
    545 9 if (!redirectUri) { 378
    546 1 throw new Error("Missing state.redirectUri"); 379
    547 } 380
    548
    549 8 if (!tokenUri) { 382
    550 1 throw new Error("Missing state.tokenUri"); 383
    551 } 384
    552
    553 7 if (!clientId) { 386
    554 1 throw new Error("Missing state.clientId"); 387
    555 } 388
    556
    557 6 const requestOptions = { 390
    558 method: "POST", 390
    559 headers: { 392
    560 "content-type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" 392
    561 }, 390
    562 body: `code=${code}&grant_type=authorization_code&redirect_uri=${encodeURIComponent(redirectUri)}` 394
    563 }; // For public apps, authentication is not possible (and thus not required), 397
    564 // since a client with no secret cannot prove its identity when it issues a 398
    565 // call. (The end-to-end system can still be secure because the client comes 399
    566 // from a known, https protected endpoint specified and enforced by the 400
    567 // redirect uri.) For confidential apps, an Authorization header using HTTP 401
    568 // Basic authentication is required, where the username is the apps 402
    569 // client_id and the password is the apps client_secret (see example). 403
    570
    571
    if (
    clientSecret
    ) {
    		 404
    572 requestOptions.headers.Authorization = "Basic " + 405
    573 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 405
    574 (0, 405
    575 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 405
    576
    577 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 405
    578 _lib 405
    579 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 405
    580 . 405
    581 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 405
    582 btoa) 405
    583 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 405
    584 (clientId + ":" + clientSecret); 405
    585 debug("Using state.clientSecret to construct the authorization header: %s", requestOptions.headers.Authorization); 408
    586 } else { 409
    587 6 debug("No clientSecret found in state. Adding the clientId to the POST body"); 410
    588 6 requestOptions.body += `&client_id=${encodeURIComponent(clientId)}`; 411
    589 } 412
    590
    591 6 return requestOptions; 414
    592 } 415

    601 async function ready(env, onSuccess, onError) { 424

    if (

    614
    615 async function init(env, options) { 436
    616 6 const url = env.getUrl(); 437
    617 6 const code = url.searchParams.get("code"); 438
    618 6 const state = url.searchParams.get("state"); // if `code` and `state` params are present we need to complete the auth flow 441
    619
    620 6 if (code && state) { 442
    621 2 return completeAuth(env); 443
    622 } // Check for existing client state. If state is found, it means a client 446
    623 // instance have already been created in this session and we should try to 447
    624 // "revive" it. 448
    625
    626
    627 4 const storage = env.getStorage(); 449
    628 4 const key = state || (await storage.get( 450
    629 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 450
    630 _settings 450
    631 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 450
    632 . 450
    633 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 450
    634 SMART_KEY 450
    635 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 450
    636 )); 450
    637 4 const cached = await storage.get(key); 451
    638
    639 4 if (cached) { 452
    640 2 return new 453
    641 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 453
    642 _Client 453
    643 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 453
    644 . 453
    645 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 453
    646 default 453
    647 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 453
    648 (env, cached); 453
    649 } // Otherwise try to launch 456
    650
    651
    652 2 return authorize(env, options).then(() => { 457
    653 // `init` promises a Client but that cannot happen in this case. The 458
    654 // browser will be redirected (unload the page and be redirected back 459
    655 // to it later and the same init function will be called again). On 460
    656 // success, authorize will resolve with the redirect url but we don't 461
    657 // want to return that from this promise chain because it is not a 462
    658 // Client instance. At the same time, if authorize fails, we do want to 463
    659 // pass the error to those waiting for a client instance. 464
    660 return new Promise(() => { 465
    661 /* leave it pending!!! */ 465
    662 }); 465
    663 }); 457
    664 } 467
